com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.sequence

Class ImmutableSequence.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.sequence.ImmutableSequence.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    ImmutableSequence

    public static class ImmutableSequence.Builder
extends Object
    Provides a system for building a list of ImmutableSequence which are even more compact than normal by analyzing patterns in the names of sequences.

    A single Builder instance should be used when importing an entire file. 2 passes need to be made of the imported file. During the first pass, addName(String) should be called for each name. On the 2nd pass, sequences can be created using createNucleotideSequence(String, CharSequence) or createNucleotideGraphSequence(String, CharSequence, NucleotideGraph) or createNucleotideGraphSequence(String, CharSequence, int[]).

    There is an overhead to creating name-compacted ImmutableSequences in performance and the permgen memory space which may cause problems if you create for example more than 10,000 little contigs each with their own Builder instance. Therefore it is recommended that this class only be used on sets of sequences of 1000 or more sequences. For smaller cases, createNucleotideSequence(String, CharSequence) should be used instead.

    This class is not thread safe.

    • Method Detail

      • addName

        public void addName(String name)
        Adds a name that will later be used in a call to create a sequence. All invocations of this method must be made before any sequences are created. For example when importing from a file, a first pass needs to be made of the file to record all names. And then during a second pass of the file, the sequences can be created using createNucleotideSequence(String, CharSequence) or createNucleotideGraphSequence(String, CharSequence, NucleotideGraph) or createNucleotideGraphSequence(String, CharSequence, int[]). This allows sequence names to be analyzed for patterns so that they can be compressed.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of a sequence. Sequence names do not need to be unique - i.e. the same name can be added multiple times.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If an of the sequence creation methods have already been called on this builder.

      • createNucleotideSequence

        public ImmutableSequence createNucleotideSequence(String name,
                                         CharSequence charSequence)
        Creates a nucleotide sequence compacted to use as little memory as possible
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the sequence, which should be identical to a name passed to an earlier call to addName(String). Sequence names do not need to be unique - i.e. the same name can be added multiple times.
        charSequence - the sequence nucleotides or residues.
        Returns:
        an immutable sequence

      • createCopyOf

        public ImmutableSequence createCopyOf(SequenceDocument sequenceToCopy,
                             boolean createCopyEvenIfItDiscardsInformation)
        Creates a ImmutableSequence copy of a given sequence.
        Parameters:
        sequenceToCopy - the sequence to create a copy of
        createCopyEvenIfItDiscardsInformation - true to create a copy even if not all information present in sequenceToCopy can be copied. For example annotations aren't supported.
        Returns:
        the created copy, or null if createCopyEvenIfItDiscardsInformation==false and the sequence to copy contains information not storable in an ImmutableSequence.
